reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 13, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars TeamGroup Delivers Excellence Again
reviews.reviewText: Embarking on numerous SSD upgrades, my journey with TeamGroup has been nothing short of exceptional. From enhancing the performance of budget laptops to optimizing my wife's PS4, TeamGroup's EX2 2TB 3D NAND TLC SSD has proven to be a versatile and affordable solution. Serving as an efficient boot drive, I reserve the faster NVMe counterparts for gaming.In the realm of SSDs, TeamGroup stands out as the epitome of reliability and affordability. Having explored alternatives, I found that other brands often fell short, succumbing to premature failures or pricing themselves out of practicality. TeamGroup, however, strikes the perfect equilibrium between cost-effectiveness and premium quality.Choosing TeamGroup is not just a purchase; it's a commitment to consistent satisfaction and peace of mind. Their products have never failed to meet, and often exceed, my expectations. TeamGroup remains my go-to choice for SSDs, embodying the essence of affordability without compromising on the paramount factor of quality. A decision to trust TeamGroup is, unequivocally, a wise investment in both performance and value.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Amazing value, good performance for a SATA III SSD. Very large writes are slow – as expected.
reviews.reviewText: I bought this 2tb SATA III internal SSD for $72. Amazing value. I was a little worried that the performance would be poor but I am getting sustained writes just below 500MB/s and sustained reads just over 500MB/s. Very, very large writes eventually slow down but I was able to get decent speeds even when writing 500gb consisting of several hundred thousand of files for a big backup task – took about 30 minutes or an average of half the smaller sustained write speed which isn't spectacular but perfectly fine. And completely expected. Reads never slow down, it's only writes that eventually get slower. In normal operation where you are writing only small amounts to the drive at any one time even if you're reading very large amounts, you will never see the speeds drop below about 500MB/s.This is a great archive, backup, and general storage drive. It can't compete with really fast modern SSDs with faster interfaces but the performance is right in line with other inexpensive SSDs using a SATA III interface. Most of those other inexpensive SSDs are more expensive than this one, sometimes a lot more expensive. I have it in a USB 3 gen1 enclosure and I can boot my computer with it just fine. It's certainly not the best boot drive but you'd pay quite a bit more for a better boot drive let alone a "best" one.Just got it today so I can't speak about longevity. The TBW specified by the manufacturer for the 2tb version which I got is pretty good. I don't plan to ever fill it up more than just a bit past halfway and it's for incremental backups so after today the writes will be pretty small and therefore I expect it will last me for as long as I care to keep it in service.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Lightning fast, reliable, easy to install
reviews.reviewText: My older HDD was failing, but it was 2 TB for my laptop.I was thinking that a 2 TB SSD was out of price range, but along came Teamgroup's very nicely priced 2 TB drive.It came with a raw format, which was perfect for cloning.The whole process from the time I took the SSD out of the box until I was firing up my refurbished computer was less than five hours. (More than 95% of that time was cloning the disk.)Now, my five year old computer runs like new.I love this SSD, and I think that you will too.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Some compatibility issues with the 4TB version
reviews.reviewText: I have a couple 1TB and below from team data and they all worked reliably for years.This 4TB disk, after reformat (full format) and using a jmicron based sata to usb enclosure, data transfer rate is 500Mbps. SanZang SATA enclosure - does not see the drive. Initially I thought that the drive defective - I could partition and format only using the sata interface - when a usb to sata adapter was used, I could not write to the disk (tried 4 different adapters). After partition and format using the sata interface, it also worked in a sata to usb enclosure using jmicron chipset (as well as wavlink usb to sata cable).

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Huge 4TB & great performance!
reviews.reviewText: It's amazing - at the time I purchased the 4TB Teamgroup QX 4TB it was under $146! And in less than ideal test condition with Crystal disk mark I got Read and Write speeds that actually slightly exceeds the "up to 560/500MB/s" description on the product info page! (The less-than-ideal is I put the drive in a very inexpensive external enclosure with USB-C 3.2 support and connected to a PC with USB-C 10gbps support.Prices on this type of product do fluctuate - but tend to go down over time, so I hope to buy more of these screaming-fast drives. (For newer machines that have M.2 sockets for NVMe, you can get faster M.2 drives, but when you need to use a SATA-drive and need lots of space, this is a great balance of excellent performance and price.
